38
00:03:46,797 --> 00:03:50,420
Dedication and naming of school buildings, facilities, and grounds.

39
00:03:51,160 --> 00:03:58,584
The school committee has sole authority over the naming and renaming of buildings, interior facilities, and grounds of the Medford Public Schools.

40
00:03:59,085 --> 00:04:03,547
The school committee recognizes that the names of school facilities must be undertaken with care and scrutiny.

41
00:04:03,928 --> 00:04:07,990
This policy is intended to ensure that names and or other wording associated

42
00:04:08,437 --> 00:04:12,940
with school facilities will promote and or be consistent with the goals of the Medford Public Schools.

43
00:04:13,640 --> 00:04:18,303
The naming process should include student, family, community and staff voices.

44
00:04:18,803 --> 00:04:33,692
When naming a school facility, preference is given to those persons, organizations and events which had a substantial impact on the education of Medford students and persons or events that reflect the increasing diversity of Medford student population.

45
00:04:34,853 --> 00:04:37,755
This guidance shall not preclude consideration of names of

46
00:04:38,215 --> 00:04:42,438
persons of local, state, or national or international significance.

47
00:04:43,038 --> 00:04:47,521
Names of persons employed by the school or city at the time of dedication shall not be considered.

48
00:04:49,002 --> 00:04:59,349
The school committee reserves the right to remove any name at any time if it is in the best interest of the district or donor to do so, or to protect the reputation of the district and or the donor.

49
00:05:01,070 --> 00:05:05,173
In order for a building, facility, playground, or school grounds to be

50
00:05:05,653 --> 00:05:10,896
named that is accompanied by a financial contribution, the following procedure shall be followed.

51
00:05:11,556 --> 00:05:15,238
Written request is placed on a regular school committee meeting agenda.

52
00:05:15,718 --> 00:05:20,741
The item should specify the intent of the requester and the details of the intended financial contribution.

53
00:05:21,362 --> 00:05:26,304
It should offer appropriate background information on the person or organization in the request.

54
00:05:27,225 --> 00:05:31,427
Two, the school committee will consider the request and invite public input on it at

55
00:05:33,125 --> 00:05:38,029
at least two consecutive meetings before a vote to approve or deny the request is taken.

56
00:05:39,290 --> 00:05:44,875
Number three, a gift between the donor and the school committee must be approved simultaneously as the name is voted.

57
00:05:46,537 --> 00:05:55,745
Either the standard agreement must specify that the building interior facility or grounds to be named, the duration of the naming period as well as payment terms.

58
00:05:55,885 --> 00:06:00,849
And these agreements will be considered for the public record and kept on file by the school committee for access by the public.

59
00:06:02,607 --> 00:06:12,293
Next section, for a building facility playground or school grounds to be named that is not accompanied by a financial contribution, the following procedure shall be followed.

60
00:06:14,134 --> 00:06:18,856
The school committee shall pass a resolution identifying the building facility or school grounds to be named.

61
00:06:19,316 --> 00:06:25,660
The school committee shall establish a naming advisory committee pursuant to policy BDF advisory committee to the school committee.

62
00:06:26,525 --> 00:06:33,309
The naming advisory committee shall adhere to the charge established in forming the committee, including public participation timelines and other criteria.

63
00:06:34,009 --> 00:06:38,591
The school committee shall receive recommendations from the naming advisory committee at a regular school committee meeting.

64
00:06:39,492 --> 00:06:43,114
The school committee shall by majority vote, adopt a name.

65
00:06:43,354 --> 00:06:48,496
The school committee is not required to accept the recommendations of the naming advisory committee.

66
00:06:50,838 --> 00:06:51,598
The next section.

67
00:06:52,068 --> 00:06:58,512
For a classroom or space within a school building to be named, the following procedures shall be followed.

68
00:06:59,613 --> 00:07:02,835
A written request is placed on a regular school committee meeting agenda.

69
00:07:03,175 --> 00:07:08,219
The item should specify the intent of the requester and the reasons why this particular name would fit the space.

70
00:07:08,379 --> 00:07:13,222
It should offer appropriate background information on the person or organization in the request.

71
00:07:13,342 --> 00:07:20,387
Number two, the school committee will consider the request and invite public input at two consecutive meetings before a vote to approve or deny the request is taken.

72
00:07:22,472 --> 00:07:25,773
The school committee may choose to send their request to a naming advisory committee.

73
00:07:27,774 --> 00:07:36,496
And then final section for a community giving program where donors will be invited to give to a project in exchange for a physical dedication.

74
00:07:36,636 --> 00:07:44,259
So for example, a brick with the donor name on it, the program rules and required donation levels will be placed on the regular school committee agenda.

75
00:07:44,619 --> 00:07:48,760
The item should describe the program placement of physical dedications, donor levels, and other rules.

76
00:07:49,382 --> 00:07:52,705
The committee will consider the request and invite public input.

77
00:07:53,285 --> 00:08:05,695
The school committee may make a decision at any time provided that public input was received prior, sorry, before the vote of approval or denial.

78
00:08:06,196 --> 00:08:10,259
So that is everything that I have taken a crack at.

79
00:08:14,523 --> 00:08:17,365
And I would love to hear what you all think

80
00:08:23,415 --> 00:08:23,935
Member Rizzo.

81
00:08:24,756 --> 00:08:25,156
Thank you.

